TITLE: Please invite me to your Super Bowl party. Pretty please?
SUMMARY: All I want for Sunday is to be surrounded by friends and family members, writes Jeff Pearlman. I will gladly trade yet another lonely day in omicron America for a bunch of happy folks united over a game between two teams 98.7% of us care very little about.

TITLE: Travel to Ireland during Covid-19: What you need to know before you go
SUMMARY: If you're planning a trip to Ireland, here's what you'll need to know and expect if you want to visit during the global coronavirus pandemic.

TITLE: Crowd fundraising site says they will defy Canadian court order to stop disbursing funds to convoy protesters
SUMMARY: Online crowd fundraising site GiveSendGo said on Twitter it will not follow a Canadian court order mandating it stop distributing funds to convoy protesters.

TITLE: An 11-year-old girl with Down syndrome was being bullied. So her country's President walked her to school
SUMMARY: The President of North Macedonia walked an 11-year-old girl with Down syndrome to school after he heard she was being bullied.

TITLE: Day 7 of the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics
SUMMARY: The 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics continue with curling, snowboarding and Men's single skating. Follow here for the latest news, results and updates.

TITLE: Blinken: Russian invasion of Ukraine 'could begin at any time'
SUMMARY: US Secretary of State Antony Blinken said Friday that a Russian invasion of Ukraine "could begin at any time," including during the Beijing Winter Olympics, and the United States continues "to see very troubling signs of Russian escalation, including new forces arriving at the Ukrainian border."

TITLE: Olympics: From clothing hauls to TikTok trends, Gen Z Olympians show new side of Games
SUMMARY: American snowboarder Maddie Mastro has captured the hearts of millions on the internet by showing both the highs and lows of being an Olympian, sharing everything from try-on hauls to competition prep on her TikTok account.

TITLE: Canadian mayor will seek a court order to move against truckers protesting at critical bridge to US
SUMMARY: A Canadian mayor plans to ask a court Friday for more authority to remove truckers from the busiest international crossing in North America as weekslong, nationwide Covid-19 protests have disrupted the supply chain and triggered a state of emergency in the country's most populous province.

TITLE: Canadian trucker protests are the latest example of Covid-19 absurdity
SUMMARY: What started out as a protest over Covid restrictions in Canada is now greatly disrupting peoples' everyday lives -- which is what the protest was supposedly aimed at stopping, writes Abdul El-Sayed

TITLE: Black FedEx driver allegedly shot at by White father and son says he sees similarities with Ahmaud Arbery case: 'I feel it's my responsibility to speak up'
SUMMARY: A Black FedEx driver who says he was shot at by a White father and son while delivering packages in Mississippi "can definitely see the similarities" between his case and that of Ahmaud Arbery, the Black man who was chased and murdered in south Georgia.

TITLE: How birds are adapting to climate crisis
SUMMARY: Birds that have bigger brains, relative to their body size, are not shrinking as much as their smaller-brained counterparts in response to climate change, according to data from tens of thousands of birds that collided with buildings in Chicago.

TITLE: Hit by realities of 50-50 Senate, Democrats turn focus to bipartisanship
SUMMARY: Democrats on Capitol Hill are pivoting away from talking about what was once was a cornerstone of their agenda -- the Build Back Better Act -- to focusing on a batch of smaller, bipartisan proposals that they hope can show voters that even a 50-50 Senate can work.

TITLE: Here's who won gold medals at the Beijing Olympics on Friday
SUMMARY: There were seven gold medals up for grabs on Thursday at the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics.

TITLE: The Canadian protesters aren't just truckers. Here's who has been showing up and what they want
SUMMARY: A massive protest by Canadian truckers and others against Covid-19 mandates has been growing for weeks, crippling three US border crossings and downtown Ottawa -- with no end in sight.

TITLE: Slovenia's Julian Alps: Explore this fairy-tale landscape
SUMMARY: Slovenia's northwestern corner is packed with spectacular landscapes of towering peaks, waterfalls, rushing rivers and pristine mountain lakes, many of which are inTriglav, the country's only national park.

TITLE: At least six people, including five officers, injured in Phoenix shooting and barricade situation
SUMMARY: At least six people, including five police officers, were injured during a shooting early Friday in a Phoenix suburb, police said.

TITLE: Amazon rolls back mask mandate for some vaccinated warehouse workers
SUMMARY: Amazon will no longer require its fully vaccinated warehouse employees to wear face masks at work in states that have eased up on mask mandates, the company said in an internal memo Thursday.

TITLE: Adele pole dances at London nightclub, sending fans crazy
SUMMARY: Who would have thought the day would come when you could see the words "Adele," "pole dancing" and "beige pantsuit" in the same sentence?

TITLE: Don't panic if you got a scary IRS notice
SUMMARY: Imagine having filed and paid your taxes on time, then months later you get a notice in the mail from the IRS suggesting you didn't. That's what's happening to many taxpayers this year thanks to automated notices being sent out from a backlogged IRS.

TITLE: Senators allege CIA collected data on Americans in warrantless searches
SUMMARY: Two Democratic members of the Senate Intelligence Committee have raised concerns about how the CIA has handled Americans' information collected incidentally as part of the agency's foreign surveillance programs, in what the lawmakers say amounts to "serious problems associated with warrantless backdoor searches of Americans."

TITLE: Watchdog investigating DHS inspector general over retaliation allegations
SUMMARY: The Department of Homeland Security Inspector General is being investigated as part of a newly revealed probe looking into allegations of retaliation, according to documents shared with CNN.

TITLE: Americans keep feeling worse about this high-inflation economy
SUMMARY: Prices keep rising, and Americans are growing concerned that Washington's policies won't do much about them.

TITLE: Long life comes from eating right, studies say. Here's how to begin
SUMMARY: Research shows that eating a plant-based diet can add years to your life. Here's how to make healthy eating a habit.

TITLE: Why the LGBTQ community loves -- and will always love -- Whitney Houston
SUMMARY: It was a performance that likely would've made Whitney Houston proud.

TITLE: Must-watch videos of the week: Super Bowl edition
SUMMARY: A high-tech stadium takes center stage, an all-time NFL great shares the screen with his son, and the real stars of the show -- the commercials -- have arrived. These are the must-watch videos of the week: Super Bowl LVI edition.

TITLE: Outgoing chief archivist at center of ERA fight and Trump documents controversy
SUMMARY: Recent controversies over the certification of the Equal Rights Amendment and improper record-keeping of Trump-era documents have pushed the nation's chief archivist, whose typical pro forma responsibilities render him unknown to all but the most knowledgeable Washingtonians, into the middle of several high-profile political dramas.

TITLE: For Shiffrin, what comes next is up to her alone
SUMMARY: Nathan Chen's gold medal in men's figure skating -- along with wins by snowboarders Lindsay Jacobells and Chloe Kim, and the struggles of skier Mikaela Shiffrin -- are moments of Olympic drama that show how athletes are rewriting the redemption narrative in the world of sport, writes Amy Bass.

TITLE: The latest on Ukraine and Russia tensions
SUMMARY: Tensions between Moscow and Kyiv are at their highest in years, with a large Russian troop buildup near the shared borders of the two former Soviet republics. Follow for live news updates.

TITLE: 'Delivering a message to the world': Fishing image wins marine conservation photography prize
SUMMARY: An image of two boats, with nets cast wide fishing for anchovies in the waters of Vietnam, has won the Save Our Seas Foundation Marine Conservation category of the Underwater Photographer of the Year 2022 award.

TITLE: Liz Cheney wants Republicans to remember what they keep trying to forget
SUMMARY: In the HBO series "The Leftovers," there is a group called the "Guilty Remnant" that seeks to remind people that 2% of the world's population suddenly disappeared. They dress in all white, smoke and generally make it impossible for people to forget what they once were -- before the departed.
